            <div type="translation">
                <p>'of <foreign xml:lang="sga">GerrÃ¡n</foreign>'</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The personal name here possibly contains the element <foreign xml:lang="sga">gerr</foreign> 'short (-haired?)' and the diminutive suffix -agni (>-an(n), <foreign xml:lang="sga">GerrÃ¡n</foreign>) (McManus1991, 107).</p>
                <p>This is one of the inscriptions listed by McManus (1991, 93-4) to be among the earliest in the corpus showing no trace of vowel affection. It may be dated to the first half, or the early second half, of the fifth century (McManus1991, 97).</p>
            </div>
